232045088.text: "The increase in NK cells seemed dasatinib specific and might be attributable to the inhibition of multiple kinases, such as c-KIT, PDGF, SRC and Src family kinases, in addition to ABL1.31 Although SRC has been reported to be associated with NK cell function and signal transduction,32 the reason underlying dasatinib induced specific increase in NK cells during consolidation in the failed patients remains unclear."
